caption: Pigalle Basketball is a lovely court in the side street of Pigalle area, the court is free and it's usually full of kids and adults showing skills and enjoying themselves. If you want to play, go before midday, afterwards it gets quite busy. I'm not a basketball fan but it's nice to watch sports and see individual skills.
If you love basketball or art, stop by this hidden court in the middle of a block. The gate is often unlocked and there‚Äôs a machine with three balls for those who want to play!
Place really awesome for playing basketball good player with good level everyone is really nice and you can play often some basketball match with most of them

This is a real site-specific, social artwork accessible (both literally and metaphorically) to all kinds of people, no matter the age, race or social background. Came here after two years and the new mural painting is probably even better than the previous. It‚Äôs always a pleasure
Great atmosphere and basketball court to hoop at. Friendly store manager who's very knowledgeable and up to date with nba league matters.

The court was beautifully designed! Great location, if anything the court was a bit smaller than I expected (but, what can we do it's Paris!), came down with a friend and played with local kids :) Recommend ballers to visit ^^
Dope colors, good execution, loved it!
Unfortunately no lights so at night you can not feel the colour vibe of this place
Closed with no apparent online notice, made the trip for nothing.

Must place go to play basketball. Met some great kids visiting there with my son. He had a great time
A dream,i really suggest to visit it U won't be disappointed

I saw this on Instagram and wanted to see it and take some pictures. Maybe on some days the fence is open but now it was locked so I couldn't take any pictures. From the other side of the street you have a gppd view thougg
